        <fn id="tbl1fn1">
          <label>a</label>
          <p>Most studies report lifetime RS as the number of live births, or children living to 5 or 15 years of age, for post-reproductive men and women. Where the mean RSs for males and females are not equal, the data have not been drawn from a closed population. The ratio of the opportunity for selection in males and females (I<sub>m</sub>: I<sub>f</sub>) takes into account the difference in average RS between males and females (the same pattern of results is found when this variable is used instead of V<sub>m</sub>: V<sub>f</sub> in the analyses regarding mating systems).</p>
